# Content Format

## File Format

- Source files are MyST Markdown (`.md`) — the only source of truth
- Executable code runs in-page via the local Jupyter server (configured in `myst.yml` under `project.jupyter`)

## Kernelspec Frontmatter (Required)

Every `.md` file that contains at least one `{code-cell}` **must** declare a kernelspec in its YAML frontmatter so MyST/Thebe can attach the correct kernel:

```yaml
---
kernelspec:
  name: python3
  display_name: Python 3
  language: python
---
```

Place this at the very top of the file (before any headings). Files without code cells do not need it.

## Executable Code Cells

All executable cells use `{code-cell} python` — the global kernel is `python3`. Cell magics select the language:

| Magic | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| *(none)* | Pure Python |
| `%%bash` | Shell commands (docker, curl, pip, git, etc.) |
| `%%sql` | Raw SQL (requires jupysql setup cell and `DATABASE_URL`) |

Examples:

````
```{code-cell} python
%%bash
docker ps
```
````

````
```{code-cell} python
%%sql
SELECT * FROM orders LIMIT 5;
```
````

### Setup cells

Lessons using `%%sql` need a hidden setup cell at the top:

````
```{code-cell} python
:tags: [remove-input]
%load_ext sql
```
````

Connection is automatic via `DATABASE_URL` (set in the lab's `compose.yml`).

### Non-executable blocks

Plain fenced blocks (` ```python `, ` ```bash `, ` ```sql `, ` ```yaml `) are illustrative only — not executed in-page.

## Lab Notes

At the top of lessons requiring a lab:

````
```{note}
This lesson requires the ORM lab. Run `make lab-orm` before starting.
```
````

## Reproducibility

- All examples must run on the workspace container (Linux-based)
- Prefer SQLite and stdlib for lessons that don't need a sidecar
- Code cells must be runnable in sequence from top to bottom
- Embed sample data in code or provide seed scripts
